modules.description: Handles asynchronous HTTP requests with customizable chunking, credentials, and body conversion. Operates on boolean flags, integers, and JavaScript strings to control request behavior. Used to configure AJAX calls for streaming data or cross-origin requests with proper encoding.

Handles HTTP request configuration for synchronous client interactions, including chunked response control, chunk size specification, and JavaScript string conversion. Operates on boolean flags, integers, and JavaScript string types. Used to customize XHR behavior in web applications requiring precise control over data transmission and encoding.

Provides asynchronous HTTP request methods (GET, POST, PUT, etc.) with support for headers, body data, and chunked transfers. Operates on HTTP responses, raw byte bodies, and context-aware operations. Enables efficient handling of large data streams and form submissions with explicit control over request configuration.

Provides functions to perform HTTP requests (GET, POST, PUT, PATCH, DELETE, HEAD) with synchronous XHR, handling raw byte responses and headers. Operates on HTTP methods, URIs, headers, and body data, with support for form submissions and context-aware calls. Ensures timely consumption of response bodies and manages request configuration through context parameters.

Provides HTTP request and response handling, parsing, and TLS-enabled server creation. Works with message structures, headers, and body streams. Used to build secure, high-performance HTTP servers with Lwt-based concurrency.

Provides functions to configure HTTP request behavior, including chunked response handling, chunk size setting, and conversion of JavaScript strings to OCaml strings. Works with boolean flags, integer values, and JavaScript string representations. Used to customize XML HTTP requests in web applications for controlled data transmission and encoding.
